///////WordPress basic setup/////////

Here’s a basic setup guide for WordPress:
---
1. Prerequisites
Before installing WordPress, make sure you have:
A domain name
A web hosting account (like Bluehost, SiteGround, or Hostinger)
PHP (v7.4+), MySQL (v5.7+ or MariaDB 10.3+), and Apache/Nginx on your server
Or, for local development:
Use XAMPP, MAMP, WAMP, or Local by Flywheel
---
2. Download WordPress
Go to wordpress.org/download
Download the latest version and extract the zip
---
3. Create a Database
Log in to phpMyAdmin
Click "New" to create a database (e.g., wordpress_db)
Choose utf8mb4_general_ci collation
---
4. Configure wp-config.php
Rename wp-config-sample.php to wp-config.php
Edit it with your database details:
define( 'DB_NAME', 'wordpress_db' );
define( 'DB_USER', 'root' );
define( 'DB_PASSWORD', '' ); // or your DB password
define( 'DB_HOST', 'localhost' );
---
5. Upload Files to Server
If local, copy files to htdocs/wordpress (XAMPP) or relevant directory
If on a web host, use FTP (like FileZilla) to upload files to your domain’s root folder
---
6. Run the Installer
Visit your site in the browser:
http://localhost/wordpress
or
https://yourdomain.com
Follow the setup wizard:
Choose language
Site title, admin username/password, email
Install
---
7. Log in
Go to https://yourdomain.com/wp-admin
Log in with the admin credentials
---
Let me know if you want help setting up a theme, plugins, or custom functionality!
